name: Bennu Rising
description:
KafeNubia Signature Logo Series T-Shirt


A heron’s call is the cry of the sacred Benu-bird that announced the beginning of time in an ancient Egyptian creation.  

A spell to transform the dead into the great Benu-bird is elaborated in The Book of the Dead.

The Benu Bird is linked to that of the phoenix. Both are birds of the sun, both are self created, rather than being born from other creatures, both undergo death and become symbols of regeneration. The Egyptian sunbird is identified with Ra, the Sun God.  The Benu was identified with the Temple of the Sun God at Heliopolis, which was revered by the Egyptians as the sacred mound from whence the Sun god, in his aspect of the Benu Bird, arose cyclically to renew Egypt; another feature which was shared by both the phoenix and the Benu Bird.

The Benu Bird was also known to be a symbol of Osiris and is said to have sprung from the heart of Osiris as a living symbol of God, thus renewing itself.
